give.n <- function(x){
  return(c(y = mean(x)*1.1, label = length(x))) 
}

          age >= 60 & age < 65 ~ "60-64",
          age >= 65 & age < 70 ~ "65-69",
          age >= 70 & age < 75 ~ "70-74",
          age >= 75 & age < 80 ~ "75-79",
          age >= 80 ~ "80 or older"))

age.total <- merge(age.population.5, age.sample, by.x = "agecat", by.y = ".")

age.total <- age.total %>% 
  rename(age.category = agecat,
  count.population = n.x,
  count.sample = n.y,
  percentage.population = percentage.x,
  percentage.sample = percentage.y)

t1 <- df.def %>% mutate(id = row_number()) %>% 
  select(experimental.group,
         id,
         credibility.EMA,
         credibility.post) %>%
  drop_na() %>%
